If you have a C# 8 switch expression such as below:

int Foo(int x) =&gt; x switch
        {
            1 =&gt; 1,
            _ =&gt; 1 + x
        };

If you highlight 1 + x and choose extract method from the context menu, it should create:

int Foo(int x) =&gt; x switch
        {
            1 =&gt; 1,
            _ =&gt; NewMethod(x)
        };

private static int NewMethod(x) =&gt; x+1;

What it actually creates is:

int Foo(int x) =&gt; NewMethod(x);

private static int NewMethod(int x)
        {
            return x switch
            {
                1 =&gt; 1,
                _ =&gt; 1 + x
            };
        }

